OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1784875679
OL,3,CUK 'ready to defend itself' after Iran
OL,4,Ccriticises US using British bases
OL,6,FPrime Minister Andy Burnham has
OL,7,Fmaintained his predecessor Sir Keir
OL,8,FStarmer's agreement to allow the US to
OL,9,Fuse British bases, including RAF
OL,10,FFairford in Gloucestershire.
OL,12,FA spokesperson for the Ministry of
OL,13,FDefence said: "Our armed forces are
OL,14,Fready to keep the United Kingdom safe
OL,15,Ffrom any kind of attacks, whether it's
OL,16,Fon our soil or from abroad. The UK
OL,17,Fstands ready 24/7 to defend itself.
OL,26,@uD@OOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
